LAGOS – As the 36 States of the federation and the Federal Capital Territory (FCT), Abuja marked the weeklong activities for the 50th anniversary of the National Youth Service Corps (NYSC) with pomp and pageantry, the Director-General, Brigadier-General Yushau Dogara Ahmed, represented by the State Coordinator, Mrs. Winifred Ngozi Shokpeka added pep to the celebration with various outdoor activities to make the celebration remarkable. The anniversary commenced with the NYSC at 50 “Unity Walk” around the major metropolis of Abeokuta, the Ogun State capital. The five-kilometre” Unity Walk” took off from the State Secretariat at Okelewo through Abeokuta under the watchful eyes of the State Traffic Unit of the Nigerian Police and terminated at the Moshood Abiola International Stadium, Kuto, Abeokuta. The theme is “NYSC: Five Decades of Fostering National Unity And Integration,” In a chat with newsmen, Mrs. Shokpeka said despite the challenges of the past 50 years, the NYSC scheme can be described as a Nigerian success story. In the same vein, the Ogun State Commissioner for Youth and Sports, Dr. Kehinde Oluwadare extolled the National Youth Service Corps for her contributions to national development and fostering unity over the past five decades. Besides the special Jumat, visit to the orphanage/juvenile home, and features on radio programmes, the Scheme also hosted an exhibition organised by the Skills Acquisition and Entrepreneurship Development (SAED) programme staged at the Okelewo, Abeokuta Secretariat of the scheme.